cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a technique to accelerate training of machine learning models on heterogeneous compute systems, which is a common topic in the machine learning community (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of primal-dual coordinate methods, which is a topic in optimization (cs.DC). The technique involves adaptivity to system memory hierarchy, which is related to data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of GPUs and FPGAs, which are common hardware accelerators in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
